30/01/2005
BUDAPEST, Hungary -- Hungary and Croatia announced Friday (28 January) that they have formally launched a joint bid to host football's European Championship in 2012. Also in the running are Italy, Greece, Romania and a joint bid from Poland and Ukraine. Europe's football governing body, UEFA, will announce its decision in December 2006. (Hina - 28/01/05; AFP - 27/01/05)
